[NPC Narrate] Oropher Telemmaite says without any hint of attitude.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: Why are you looking for these answers?
[NPC Internal] Well, a Guard in Ojaveda who stands near the gates asked me to try to find out, so, well, I am!
[NPC Narrate] Oropher Telemmaite closes his eyes for a long minute.
[NPC Narrate] -He opens them and says.-
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: These stories and histories are important to us all, citizen.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: Talk to a woodworker about who carved the gates.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: Talk to...
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: someone who might be most knowledgeable about that history, of when the legend began.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: And the why?
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: Why serpents and eagle gates in the Enkidukai Dsar?
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: Well, after you find those first answers, come back and ask me again.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: If you are careful in your inquiry and...
[NPC Narrate] Oropher Telemmaite looks directly at you.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: And be honest with me, then perhaps the mystery will become clear.
[NPC Internal] I think I've found some things out. Will you help me now please?
[NPC Narrate] Oropher Telemmaite smiles a slow smile.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: First tell me, do you know who carved the gates?
[NPC Internal] Yes, Gorbiak told me who carved them.
[NPC Narrate] Oropher Telemmaite smiles and says.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: And did the good gobble tell you anything else?
[NPC Internal] Yes he said to talk to an old person a Dermorian and Octarch guard, that would be you, right?
[NPC Narrate] Oropher Telemmaite laughs a resonant laugh that fills and echoes through the Hall.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: Well I suppose that definition fits me.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: Yes.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: So he told you the gobbles themselves carved the gates, didn't he?
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: That is true.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: It was a long, long time ago.
[NPC Internal] So, I know who carved the gates, the gobbles. I know when, kinda, just that it was a long, long time ago. And it was about the time the Lemurs came to the Dome, I guess. But I don't know why the gobbles carved the gates? And why Serpents and Eagles, I mean I know the gobble tribes call themselves Serpents and Eagles. But the carvings are of real serpents, like, snakes! And real eagles, that fly! I don't understand it. Can you clear this mystery up please?
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: Yes my Klyros friend.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: I could tell you why.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: But it might be better to hear the story from its source, perhaps?
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: From...
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: Those...who were there.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: From those who have long memories.
[NPC] Oropher Telemmaite: You know, YOU, those Ojaveda Gates are as old as the hills.
